cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about visual recognition using deep learning models, specifically a Generative-Discriminative Variational Model (GDVM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses overfitting and training techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a latent variable for generative abilities, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper considers multi-label classification and zero-shot learning, which could also place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
